The paper proposes a modification of the Alternating Least Squares (ALS) algorithm for tensor decomposition that is theoretically principled and practically superior to traditional ALS. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories, as these are the most relevant areas for tensor decomposition. Additionally, the paper involves the use of incoherence assumptions on the factors of the tensor, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the use of tensor completion, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.IT, and cs.NA.
